This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of multilingual NMT methods, which involves training models on multiple languages, and this could potentially fall under the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pre-specified text domains, which could involve techniques from "Neural Networks" (cs.NE) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) to identify and classify the domains.
